## ğŸŒ Insights Summary
- **Python** remains the most popular programming language among data professionals.  
- **Data Scientists** tend to have the highest average salaries.  
- Respondents report **moderate work-life balance (5.7/10)** and **lower salary satisfaction (4.3/10)**.  
- Gender gaps in salaries remain visible but vary by country and role.

